Yesterday my son donated his stem cells for a second time to his cousin & Sawyer got special permission to come surprise Remy yesterday during his extraction 😊. Prefer to be on the other side of the lens but I have to share about these goggles because @vallon_official nailed them! Most of you don’t know but I’m blind in my left eye. I’ve always struggled with ski goggles because they usually constrict my vision even more until now because @vallon_official paired up with Carl Zeiss & made the ultimate lenses: + Lens-range developed with Carl Zeiss combining blue-light blocking brown tint with anti-reflective mirror coating for exceptional clarity and depth perception.
+ Spherical lens construction offering a maximized field of vision and 100% UV protection.
+ Dual-layered lens engineered from an outer lens from ZEISS and an inner anti-fog lens from Mazzuchelli. 

I could finally see more & they never fogged! So glad I said yes to this collaboration! Seriously go check them out.

“Aunt Janelle, I’m cancer free!” … were the words I heard on the other end of the phone this week from my nephew Sawyer! Over a year after I shared his second relapse, more chemo, radiation & second stem cell transplant… the miracle we’d been waiting for has finally arrived! This kid has beaten leukemia 3 times in 5 years now! He is a true warrior ❤️. #goodvibes #goodbyecancer

1 year! Yesterday marked the second stem cell transplant between these two. We are continuing to fist bump to Sawyer being healthy & still in full remission! It’s been a year of being at home, in school with friends, first plane rides to Disney and making the best memories. We are so grateful & remain hopeful his battle days are over. Tomorrow Sawyer will head to his children’s hospital for his 1 year post stem cell transplant appointment. It will be a long day of tests from checking his lung function, to looking at his heart, and of course what we pray is his very last bone marrow biopsy to make sure he is still in deep remission.
